------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. AUTHORIZED USE
------------------------------------------------------------------------

You MAY use obfush for:

  - Source-code obfuscation of bash scripts you own or are explicitly
    authorized to obfuscate as part of a sanctioned engagement.
  - Anti-reverse-engineering hardening of red team payloads under a
    formal rules-of-engagement document.
  - Security research, detection engineering, and defensive tooling
    evaluation.
  - Educational analysis in controlled lab environments.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. PROHIBITED USE
------------------------------------------------------------------------

You MAY NOT use obfush for:

  - Unauthorized intrusion into any system, network, or service.
  - Distribution of malware, ransomware, or any payload intended to
    cause harm to systems or persons not authorized for testing.
  - Evasion of monitoring on systems where you do not have explicit,
    written authorization from the system owner.
  - Any activity that violates local, national, or international law.
  - Mass targeting, supply chain compromise, or detection-evasion
    in support of malicious operations.

The authors disclaim any responsibility for misuse. Use of this tool
outside an authorized engagement is the sole responsibility of the
